rcle">inscribed circle</a>. That is, there exists a circle that is <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tangent" title=3D"Tangent">tangent</a> to=
 all four sides. Additionally, if a convex kite is not a rhombus, there is =
a circle outside the kite that is tangent to the extensions of the four sid=
es; therefore, every convex kite that is not a rhombus is an <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ex-tangential_quadrilateral" title=3D"Ex-tangent=
ial quadrilateral">ex-tangential quadrilateral</a>. The convex kites that a=
re not rhombi are exactly the quadrilaterals that are both tangential and e=
x-tangential.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-alsina-nelson_17-4" class=3D"reference"><a=
