son-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup> For every <i>concave</i> kite there exist two circles t=
angent to two of the sides and the extensions of the other two: one is inte=
rior to the kite and touches the two sides opposite from the concave angle,=
 while the other circle is exterior to the kite and touches the kite on the=
