<p>All kites <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tessellation" title=
=3D"Tessellation">tile the plane</a> by repeated <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Point_reflection" title=3D"Point reflection">point reflectio=
n</a> around the midpoints of their edges, as do more generally all quadril=
aterals.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-schattschneider_34-0" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kite_(geometry)#cite_note-schattschneid=
er-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> Kites and darts with angles 72=C2=B0, 72=C2=B0, 72=C2=B0=
, 144=C2=B0 and 36=C2=B0, 72=C2=B0, 36=C2=B0, 216=C2=B0, respectively, form=
 the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prototile" title=3D"Prototile=
">prototiles</a> of one version of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Penrose_tiling" title=3D"Penrose tiling">Penrose tiling</a>, an <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aperiodic_tiling" title=3D"Aperiodic til=
ing">aperiodic tiling</a> of the plane discovered by mathematical physicist=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roger_Penrose" title=3D"Roger Pen=
rose">Roger Penrose</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-gardner_5-1" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kite_(geometry)#cite_note-gardne=
r-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup> When a kite has angles that, at its apex and one side, sum =
to <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"=
mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math=
