class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kite_(geometry=
)#cite_note-fathauer-35"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> These rosettes can be used to study th=
e phenomenon of inelastic collapse, in which a system of moving particles m=
eeting in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inelastic_collision" tit=
le=3D"Inelastic collision">inelastic collisions</a> all coalesce at a commo=
n point.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-chazelle-karntikoon-zheng_36-0" class=3D"refere=
